# Flip a fair coin three times. How often do you get heads exactly twice — no more, no less?
# There are 3 ways to do it (HHT, HTH, THH) out of 8 equally likely outcomes, so 3/8 = 0.375.
# Flip a fair coin three times and count the heads; ask how often that count is exactly two.
coin  = rand::bernoulli(0.5);
flips ~[3] coin;
heads = vec::count(flips);
Print("P(exactly two heads of three) =", P(heads == 2))
# See the whole shape: 0, 1, 2, or 3 heads — the bar at 2 is the 3/8 we asked about.
plot::histogram(heads)
